verses.text_plain: Behold my servant, whom I uphold; mine elect, in whom my soul delighteth; I have put my spirit upon him: he shall bring forth judgment to the Gentiles.
verses.verse_html: 1Behold my servant, whom I uphold; mine elect, in whom my soul delighteth; I have put my spirit upon him: he shall bring forth judgment to the Gentiles.

tokens.text: upon him: he shall bring forth

verses.text_plain: He shall not cry, nor lift up, nor cause his voice to be heard in the street.
verses.verse_html: 2He shall not cry, nor lift up, nor cause his voice to be heard in the street.

verses.text_plain: A bruised reed shall he not break, and the smoking flax shall he not quench: he shall bring forth judgment unto truth.
verses.verse_html:
3A bruised reed shall he not break, and the smoking flax shall he not quench: he shall bring forth judgment unto truth. ▼
▼ smoking: or, dimly burning
 , ▼
▼ quench: Heb. quench it

footnotes.body_html: ▼ smoking: or, dimly burning
▼ quench: Heb. quench it

verses.text_plain: He shall not fail nor be discouraged, till he have set judgment in the earth: and the isles shall wait for his law.
verses.verse_html:
4He shall not fail nor be discouraged, till he have set judgment in the earth: and the isles shall wait for his law. ▼
▼ discouraged: Heb. broken

verses.text_plain: Thus saith God the Lord, he that created the heavens, and stretched them out; he that spread forth the earth, and that which cometh out of it; he that giveth breath unto the people upon it, and spirit to them that walk therein:
verses.verse_html: 5Thus saith God the Lord, he that created the heavens, and stretched them out; he that spread forth the earth, and that which cometh out of it; he that giveth breath unto the people upon it, and spirit to them that walk therein:

verses.text_plain: I the Lord have called thee in righteousness, and will hold thine hand, and will keep thee, and give thee for a covenant of the people, for a light of the Gentiles;
verses.verse_html: 6I the Lord have called thee in righteousness, and will hold thine hand, and will keep thee, and give thee for a covenant of the people, for a light of the Gentiles;

verses.text_plain: To open the blind eyes, to bring out the prisoners from the prison, and them that sit in darkness out of the prison house.
verses.verse_html: 7To open the blind eyes, to bring out the prisoners from the prison, and them that sit in darkness out of the prison house.

verses.text_plain: I am the Lord: that is my name: and my glory will I not give to another, neither my praise to graven images.
verses.verse_html: 8I am the Lord: that is my name: and my glory will I not give to another, neither my praise to graven images.

verses.text_plain: Behold, the former things are come to pass, and new things do I declare: before they spring forth I tell you of them.
verses.verse_html: 9Behold, the former things are come to pass, and new things do I declare: before they spring forth I tell you of them.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise from the end of the earth, ye that go down to the sea, and all that is therein; the isles, and the inhabitants thereof.
verses.verse_html:
10Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise from the end of the earth, ye that go down to the sea, and all that is therein; the isles, and the inhabitants thereof. ▼
▼ all…: Heb. the fulness thereof

footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: Heb. the fulness thereof

verses.text_plain: Let the wilderness and the cities thereof lift up their voice, the villages that Kedar doth inhabit: let the inhabitants of the rock sing, let them shout from the top of the mountains.
verses.verse_html: 11Let the wilderness and the cities thereof lift up their voice, the villages that Kedar doth inhabit: let the inhabitants of the rock sing, let them shout from the top of the mountains.

verses.text_plain: Let them give glory unto the Lord, and declare his praise in the islands.
verses.verse_html: 12Let them give glory unto the Lord, and declare his praise in the islands.

verses.text_plain: The Lord shall go forth as a mighty man, he shall stir up jealousy like a man of war: he shall cry, yea, roar; he shall prevail against his enemies.
verses.verse_html:
13The Lord shall go forth as a mighty man, he shall stir up jealousy like a man of war: he shall cry, yea, roar; he shall prevail against his enemies. ▼
▼ prevail: or, behave himself mightily

footnotes.body_html: ▼ prevail: or, behave himself mightily

verses.text_plain: I have long time holden my peace; I have been still, and refrained myself: now will I cry like a travailing woman; I will destroy and devour at once.
verses.verse_html:
14I have long time holden my peace; I have been still, and refrained myself: now will I cry like a travailing woman; I will destroy and devour at once. ▼
▼ devour: Heb. swallow, or, sup up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ devour: Heb. swallow, or, sup up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ devour: Heb. swallow, or, sup up

verses.text_plain: I will make waste mountains and hills, and dry up all their herbs; and I will make the rivers islands, and I will dry up the pools.
verses.verse_html: 15I will make waste mountains and hills, and dry up all their herbs; and I will make the rivers islands, and I will dry up the pools.

verses.text_plain: And I will bring the blind by a way that they knew not; I will lead them in paths that they have not known: I will make darkness light before them, and crooked things straight. These things will I do unto them, and not forsake them.
verses.verse_html:
16And I will bring the blind by a way that they knew not; I will lead them in paths that they have not known: I will make darkness light before them, and crooked things straight. These things will I do unto them, and not forsake them. ▼
▼ straight: Heb. into straightness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ straight: Heb. into straightness

verses.text_plain: They shall be turned back, they shall be greatly ashamed, that trust in graven images, that say to the molten images, Ye are our gods.
verses.verse_html: 17They shall be turned back, they shall be greatly ashamed, that trust in graven images, that say to the molten images, Ye are our gods.

verses.text_plain: Hear, ye deaf; and look, ye blind, that ye may see.
verses.verse_html: 18Hear, ye deaf; and look, ye blind, that ye may see.

verses.text_plain: Who is blind, but my servant? or deaf, as my messenger that I sent? who is blind as he that is perfect, and blind as the Lord’s servant?
verses.verse_html: 19Who is blind, but my servant? or deaf, as my messenger that I sent? who is blind as he that is perfect, and blind as the Lord’s servant?

verses.text_plain: Seeing many things, but thou observest not; opening the ears, but he heareth not.
verses.verse_html: 20Seeing many things, but thou observest not; opening the ears, but he heareth not.

verses.text_plain: The Lord is well pleased for his righteousness’ sake; he will magnify the law, and make it honourable.
verses.verse_html:
21The Lord is well pleased for his righteousness’ sake; he will magnify the law, and make it honourable. ▼
▼ it: or, him

verses.text_plain: But this is a people robbed and spoiled; they are all of them snared in holes, and they are hid in prison houses: they are for a prey, and none delivereth; for a spoil, and none saith, Restore.
verses.verse_html:
22But this is a people robbed and spoiled; they are all of them snared in holes, and they are hid in prison houses: they are for a prey, and none delivereth; for a spoil, and none saith, Restore. ▼
▼ they are all…: or, in snaring all the young men of them
 , ▼
▼ for a spoil: Heb. a treading

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they are all…: or, in snaring all the young men of them
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they are all…: or, in snaring all the young men of them

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for a spoil: Heb. a treading
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for a spoil: Heb. a treading

verses.text_plain: Who among you will give ear to this? who will hearken and hear for the time to come?
verses.verse_html:
23Who among you will give ear to this? who will hearken and hear for the time to come? ▼
▼ for…: Heb. for the after time?

tokens.text: Who among you will give ear

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for…: Heb. for the after time?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for…: Heb. for the after time?

verses.text_plain: Who gave Jacob for a spoil, and Israel to the robbers? did not the Lord, he against whom we have sinned? for they would not walk in his ways, neither were they obedient unto his law.
verses.verse_html: 24Who gave Jacob for a spoil, and Israel to the robbers? did not the Lord, he against whom we have sinned? for they would not walk in his ways, neither were they obedient unto his law.

verses.text_plain: Therefore he hath poured upon him the fury of his anger, and the strength of battle: and it hath set him on fire round about, yet he knew not; and it burned him, yet he laid it not to heart.
verses.verse_html: 25Therefore he hath poured upon him the fury of his anger, and the strength of battle: and it hath set him on fire round about, yet he knew not; and it burned him, yet he laid it not to heart.

tokens.text: and it hath set him on fire
